 texts from the nineteenth century to the present, Lima dissects the ways in which the Latino body has been imagined, dismembered, and reimagined anew, providing one of the first comprehensive accounts of the construction of Latino cultural identity in the United States.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAmerican literaturexMexican American authorsxHistory and criticism. 0aChicano movement. 0aMexican American literature (Spanish). 0aMexican Americans in literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aMexican AmericansxEthnic identity. 0aMexican AmericansxHistoriography. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Hispanic American Studies.2bisacsh  aAnalyzing.  aLatino.  aLima.  aStates.  aUnites.  aaccounts.  aanew.  aartistic.  abeen.  abody.  acentury.  acomprehensive.  aconstruction.  acultural.  adismembered.  adissects.  afirst.  afrom.  aidentity.  aimagined.  aliterary.  anineteenth.  apopular.  apresent.  aproviding.  areimagined.  atexts.  avariety.  aways.  awhich.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081475214240uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814765074.001.000140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814765074423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814765074/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK